records.addlTxt: Court officer contacted Jail. (Warrant canceled by Court officer/Deputy Ripczinski w/Deputy Walter on 02/23/22 @ 11:10 am)  Downloaded and processed document from Sharefile, pulled card (sent to Sheriff's Dept).

11:09 AM   Judge John Yackel appears by video from Sawyer County.  Defendant Nina Lynn Young in court with attorney Jamy Richard Johansen, appearing by video.  Kenneth N. Sortedahl appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls case and recites appearances.  Court quashes warrant and reviews off the record discussion, indicates agreement reached.  State and Atty Johansen agree.  Atty Johansen indicates PLQ is in process of being filed, has gone over with DEF.  DEF agrees, verifies address and DOB.  DEF enters NC plea.    DEF advised of rights and penalties; DEF waives rights; parties stipulate to facts.  Court accepts plea and finds DEF guilty of count #1.  State makes a statement prior to sentencing, asking Court to accept joint recommendation.  Atty Johansen has  no comment prior to sentencing.  DEF has no comment prior to sentencing.  Court to follow agreement.  Court instructs DEF to provide DNA sample & DEF receives DNA instruction card.
